article.description: LaSondra Barrett scored 14 points and all 11 Lady Tigers in uniform hit from the field as No. 20 LSU routed winless Arkansas-Pine Bluff 80-28 on Monday night.
article.headline: LSU gets scoring from 11 players in drubbing of Arkansas-Pine Bluff
article.linkText: LSU unloads on Ark.-Pine Bluff for 52-point win
article.story:
BATON ROUGE, La. --  LaSondra Barrett scored 14 points and all 11 Lady Tigers in uniform hit from the field as LSU (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) routed winless Arkansas-Pine Bluff 80-28 on Monday night.

Adrienne Webb added 12 points and Theresa Plaisance scored 11 for LSU (3-1). Barrett hit five of six shots, made four of five free throws and grabbed seven rebounds.

Lakendra Marsh scored 13 points for the Golden Lions (0-4), who turned the ball over 35 times.

LSU broke the game open with a 27-2 run in the first half that gave the Lady Tigers a 32-6 lead.

Arkansas-Pine Bluff made only three of its first 19 shots and the Lady Tigers led 47-8 at halftime, setting an LSU record for the fewest points allowed in a half.
